They objected to the word Absolution. So the phrase ' or the remission of sins ' was added. But Absolution remained. They objected to the word Confirmation. So the phrase ' or the laying on of hands upon children baptized and able to render an account of their faith according to the Catechism following ' were added. But Confirmation remained. Other changes in the Book were equally minor except for the new section on the Sacraments added to the Catechism.